<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">Important: Don’t install using “brew” or “MacPorts” !!!</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;">Installation</span></div><div>The pip is already installed if you are using </div><div>Python 2.x &gt;= 2.7.9   </div><div>Python 3.x &gt;= 3.4 </div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> python2</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">Python 2.7.10 (v2.7.10:15c95b7d81dc, May 23 2015, 09:33:12)</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">[GCC 4.2.1 (Apple Inc. build 5666) (dot 3)] on darwin</span></div><div># Although my verion suppose to have the pip installed, I could</div><div># not found neither in <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/loca/bin</span> nor in <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/bin</span></div><div>Step 1: Download the “get-pip.py” from here: <a href="https://pip.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installing/">https://pip.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installing/</a></div><div>             save in<span style="font-size: 18px; color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> </span><span style="font-size: 18px; color: rgb(148, 17, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">/Users/khasanov/MAC_Software/PIP</span></div><div>Step 2: =&gt; cd /Users/khasanov/MAC_Software/PIP</div><div>            =&gt; sudo python2 get-pip.py</div><div>            # This will install the pip and puts the binary files in </div><div>             <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/bin</span></div><div>            # =&gt; sudo ln -s  <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/bin/pip2 /usr/local/bin/pip2</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> python3</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">Python 3.6.1 (default, Jun 25 2017, 02:28:47)</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">[GCC 4.2.1 Compatible Apple LLVM 8.0.0 (clang-800.0.42.1)] on darwin</span></div><div># No need to install fro this version</div><div>=&gt; sudo ln -s <span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/pip3.6 <span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/pip3</span></span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;">The Binary Locations</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/bin/pip2 -&gt; /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/bin/pip2</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">/usr/local/bin/pip2.7 -&gt; /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/bin/pip2.7</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/pip3.6</span><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"> (no link)</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">/usr/local/bin/pip3 -&gt; /usr/local/bin/pip3.6</span></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt;  </div></en-note>